==Finding a suitable location==
[[File:en/Manual/Dock construction 1.png|right|frame|The oil refinery where we'll be constructing a dock.]]
First, you'll need to find an oil rig and an oil refinery to which you want to bring the oil from the rig. The good thing about oil rigs is that they have a built-in dock so you don't need to construct one there. The only dock you need is at the oil refinery. Those always sit at the side of the map.

Found an oil refinery close to the waterside? Good.


==Building a dock==
[[File:en/Manual/Dock toolbar.png|frame|right|The Dock construction toolbar]]
[[File:en/Manual/Dock construction 2.png|frame|right|After some [[en/Manual/Landscaping|terraforming]], we've found a suitable location for our dock. Note the acceptance of Oil in the Waterways construction window.]]
#Open the ''Waterways construction'' toolbar by clicking the [[File:en/Manual/Manual html m2cc0c4cd.png]] button.
#Click on the ''Build ship dock'' button [[File:en/Manual/Build dock.png]]. A ''Dock building window'' will appear. Remember, you can right click on any button if you ever want a description of what it does.
#Move the mouse along the edge of the water: the dock needs to be placed on a sloped tile that is connected to a water tile.
#Keep an eye on the ''Dock building window'' and make sure that ''Oil'' is displayed after ''Accepts'' before building the dock.
#If the cursor displayes two white squares '''and''' oil is accepted at the location you picked, just click with the left mouse button to place the dock (possibly you'll have to [[en/Manual/Landscaping|terraform]] a bit first in order to create a suitable location).

[[File:en/Manual/Dock construction 3.png|frame|right|Our newly constructed dock.]]
And that's all there is to building a dock! In order to buy a ship to transport the oil, you'll have to construct a ship depot first.


